The relative risk (RR) represents the aggregation risk of the cluster compared with the rest of the regions. RR is defined as the estimated risk within the cluster divided by the estimated risk outside the cluster. The mathematical notation is as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
